1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:04,236
               ♪♪

2
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:07,573
                     Ahem! Where
                      ya goin?

3
00:00:07,775 --> 00:00:12,544
Since you three were unable to
retrieve my Bewitching Bell,

4
00:00:12,646 --> 00:00:15,848
we need another source
of great magical power

5
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:18,517
to defeat Twilight
and her friends.

6
00:00:21,055 --> 00:00:24,356
      <i> ♪ [plodding music] ♪</i>

7
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,191
           He's gone!

8
00:00:27,028 --> 00:00:28,327
              I don't trust him.

9
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:29,746
         None of us do.

10
00:00:29,847 --> 00:00:32,364
Which is why double-crossing
him with his own bell

11
00:00:32,466 --> 00:00:34,633
     will be so satisfying.

12
00:00:34,735 --> 00:00:37,402
              <i>If</i> we can figure
              out how to use it.

13
00:00:37,504 --> 00:00:38,570
    Hmmm.

14
00:00:40,441 --> 00:00:43,108
        Twilight Sparkle
        may be the worst....

15
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,977
    But she does know stuff.

16
00:00:45,079 --> 00:00:46,745
      She once said the
      archives in Canterlot

17
00:00:46,847 --> 00:00:48,747
     has a restricted area.

18
00:00:48,949 --> 00:00:52,017
     Celestia and Luna love
     to hoard information

19
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:55,955
   for themselves. If there's
   an answer, it's there.

20
00:00:56,157 --> 00:00:58,891
     My triumphant
      return to Canterlot?

21
00:00:59,093 --> 00:01:01,360
    I like the sound of that...

22
00:01:01,462 --> 00:01:03,462
     Oh my gosh! Road trip!

23
00:01:42,303 --> 00:01:46,238
               ♪♪

24
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:48,840
    Sorry to interrupt. We
    know you're busy planning

25
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:53,012
   The Summer Sun Celebration
     as we requested. But..

26
00:01:53,114 --> 00:01:55,881
              Oh! Things seem...
              calmer

27
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:57,617
                 than we would
                 have expected.

28
00:01:57,919 --> 00:01:59,118
No complaints here.

29
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:01,253
With the exception of
the odd trivia night,

30
00:02:01,355 --> 00:02:02,621
I've made a lot
of progress

31
00:02:02,723 --> 00:02:04,857
since the Royal
Swanifying Ceremony.

32
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:08,594
You may not know this about me,
but I occasionally freak out!

33
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:11,563
That was a joke. I
wanted to show you

34
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:13,132
         with the Summer
         Sun Celebration

35
00:02:13,234 --> 00:02:17,036
   how much I've improved.
   So I focused on delegating

36
00:02:17,138 --> 00:02:19,405
      and trusting others!
      It's been GREAT!

37
00:02:19,707 --> 00:02:22,842
      That's.. actually what we
      came to talk to you about.

38
00:02:22,944 --> 00:02:25,211
          This may be the last
          Summer Sun Celebration

39
00:02:25,313 --> 00:02:26,979
            you'll need to plan.

40
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:28,781
    Did I do something wrong?

41
00:02:28,883 --> 00:02:31,450
    Of course not. It's just
    that the Celebration

42
00:02:31,552 --> 00:02:34,553
      has always been about
     us. My defeat of Luna...

43
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:36,956
              And, thanks to you
               and your friends,

44
00:02:37,058 --> 00:02:38,891
                 my reunion with
                 my sister.

45
00:02:38,993 --> 00:02:40,960
Now that we're leaving,
we don't see a need

46
00:02:41,062 --> 00:02:42,594
   for the holiday any longer.

47
00:02:42,696 --> 00:02:43,647
       Now that you're...?

48
00:02:43,748 --> 00:02:47,099
  My sister and I have decided
  the time for us to retire

49
00:02:47,201 --> 00:02:49,702
    is upon us. You and
    your friends have proven

50
00:02:49,804 --> 00:02:51,771
        you are ready to
         lead Equestria.

51
00:02:52,473 --> 00:02:55,507
     So let this be the last
     Summer Sun Celebration

52
00:02:55,609 --> 00:02:59,812
   as Equestria leaves behind
   the old to embrace the new.

53
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:08,054
        My goodness! How are YOU
        feeling about all this?

54
00:03:08,256 --> 00:03:10,089
Something like this could
definitely send you

55
00:03:10,191 --> 00:03:11,991
into full
freaky-outy mode.

56
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:15,761
  I'm actually fine. But if
  this is going to be the last

57
00:03:15,863 --> 00:03:18,197
     Summer Sun Celebration,
     I want to make sure

58
00:03:18,299 --> 00:03:20,466
          it's the best
        Celebration <i>ever</i>.

59
00:03:20,968 --> 00:03:21,834
        Please don't give
        us more work...

60
00:03:21,936 --> 00:03:23,636
               Please don't give
               us more work.....

61
00:03:23,938 --> 00:03:25,437
     So even though
      everything was done,

62
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,073
       I thought of a few
       last-minute changes

63
00:03:27,175 --> 00:03:28,407
        I could use
         your help with.

64
00:03:28,609 --> 00:03:30,309
         Gah! I knew it!

65
00:03:30,411 --> 00:03:33,279
Discord: Oh! The end
of a beloved holiday?

66
00:03:33,381 --> 00:03:35,647
Last-minute changes
to a celebration?

67
00:03:35,849 --> 00:03:37,716
That sounds positively...

68
00:03:37,818 --> 00:03:39,051
Chaotic!

69
00:03:39,153 --> 00:03:40,786
    What are YOU doing here?

70
00:03:40,888 --> 00:03:44,156
I've known Celestia and Luna
longer than any of you!

71
00:03:44,258 --> 00:03:47,493
I terrorized them; they
turned me into stone...

72
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,831
        If this is the last
         Summer Sun Situation,

73
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:53,733
     I simply can't miss it.

74
00:03:54,035 --> 00:03:56,769
Well, I see I've arrived
just in time for the

75
00:03:56,971 --> 00:03:59,171
"Twilight gives her
friends an impossibly long

76
00:03:59,273 --> 00:04:02,208
and overly detailed
list" predicament!

77
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:04,977
    I guess some-draconequis
   isn't the know-it-all

78
00:04:05,079 --> 00:04:06,212
        he thinks he is!

79
00:04:06,414 --> 00:04:10,149
               ♪♪

80
00:04:10,251 --> 00:04:11,517
           <i>This</i> is it?

81
00:04:11,619 --> 00:04:12,284
              What?

82
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:14,854
      We were kinda with
      Discord on this one...

83
00:04:14,956 --> 00:04:17,823
      No more crazy lists.
      No more freaking out.

84
00:04:17,925 --> 00:04:20,159
     With your help, I
      know we've got this.

85
00:04:20,261 --> 00:04:23,795
Oh! Character
growth is so boring.

86
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:26,131
Do I at least get
my own note card?

87
00:04:29,003 --> 00:04:32,304
      There. Now, I need to
      go rewrite my speech,

88
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:34,140
     but if you all look at
     your cards, you'll see-

89
00:04:34,242 --> 00:04:37,376
Can't talk now! Have so much
to get done before sunrise!

90
00:04:44,351 --> 00:04:47,787
    Why are so many ponies up
   in the middle of the night?

91
00:04:47,889 --> 00:04:49,989
  It's that silly sun holiday.

92
00:04:50,091 --> 00:04:53,926
How many holidays do you
ponies HAVE? No matter.

93
00:04:54,028 --> 00:04:56,428
Getting into the castle
won't be a problem.

94
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:59,131
                Are you sure
                about that?

95
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:01,934
          <i> ♪ [sting] ♪</i>

96
00:05:05,706 --> 00:05:09,074
       Oh. Those are
        new. But even so...

97
00:05:11,512 --> 00:05:14,814
   <i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

98
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:20,653
     Transfer. Have to
      head inside. Open up.

99
00:05:20,855 --> 00:05:23,388
   <i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

100
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:25,724
          <i> ♪ [chimes] ♪</i>

101
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:28,360
   <i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

102
00:05:29,730 --> 00:05:31,064
        Right. Of course. Heh.

103
00:05:34,101 --> 00:05:36,302
 Uh, do yours get glitchy, too?

104
00:05:37,204 --> 00:05:39,605
      More medallions, more
      problems. Am I right?

105
00:05:41,876 --> 00:05:44,043
   They've increased
    security into the castle.

106
00:05:44,145 --> 00:05:46,946
   This is going to be more
   challenging than I thought.

107
00:05:48,983 --> 00:05:52,284
   Could you NOT go popping us
   all over the place please?

108
00:05:52,386 --> 00:05:55,688
      Time is of the
     essence! Let's.. go team!

109
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:59,458
    We need to know what we're
   doing before we go and do it.

110
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,493
Pinkie, you and I
are givin' Braeburn

111
00:06:01,595 --> 00:06:03,963
 and the Appleoosan ponies
  some adjustments to the menu.

112
00:06:04,065 --> 00:06:06,332
  Fluttershy and I are meeting
  the pegasi from Cloudsdale

113
00:06:06,434 --> 00:06:07,933
      to give them changes
      to the weather.

114
00:06:08,235 --> 00:06:11,203
  Spike, we're going to update
  The Flaming Sky Firework

115
00:06:11,305 --> 00:06:13,639
     unicorn troupe with
     Twilight's new vision.

116
00:06:13,741 --> 00:06:15,374
And I'm supposed to...

117
00:06:15,576 --> 00:06:19,912
Make sure Discord doesn't
do anything.. <i>Discord-y</i>!?

118
00:06:20,014 --> 00:06:22,281
Well, that's
annoyingly specific...

119
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:30,522
Increased security on a
crowded holiday with Twilight

120
00:06:30,624 --> 00:06:35,094
and their friends bumbling
around? This is impossible!

121
00:06:35,196 --> 00:06:39,665
    Oh, no. This is perfect!
    We need a distraction

122
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:42,835
   and those ridiculous
   ponies just gave it to us!

123
00:06:42,937 --> 00:06:45,871
         Now, do exactly
         as I tell you...

124
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:52,911
               ♪♪

125
00:06:53,013 --> 00:06:56,381
   Step away from the wagons!
   Official food tasters here

126
00:06:56,483 --> 00:06:58,317
        on official
     food-tasting business!

127
00:07:01,189 --> 00:07:03,822
     Huh. It ain't gonna be easy,

128
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:05,724
     but I think we can whip
     up these new cookies

129
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:07,593
         Twilight wants
         before sunrise.

130
00:07:07,895 --> 00:07:10,729
 If anypony can handle some
  last-minute bakin', Braeburn,

131
00:07:10,831 --> 00:07:11,764
it's y'all.

132
00:07:13,134 --> 00:07:14,933
     We brought plenty
      for the celebration,

133
00:07:15,235 --> 00:07:18,170
       but if she keeps testin',
       we might be in trouble.

134
00:07:21,442 --> 00:07:24,376
   But I see a
   suspicious-looking COOKIE!!

135
00:07:29,116 --> 00:07:31,149
       <i> ♪ [scary music] ♪</i>

136
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,820
You OK?

137
00:07:34,722 --> 00:07:37,656
I feel... weak
all of a sudden.

138
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:41,526
♪♪

139
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:43,194
     Is somepony back there?

140
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:47,165
               ♪♪

141
00:07:49,703 --> 00:07:50,535
                     What is it!?

142
00:07:50,637 --> 00:07:53,672
       Everypony! Get
       away from the food

143
00:07:53,874 --> 00:07:56,975
       till we figure out
       what's goin' on!

144
00:08:07,321 --> 00:08:09,621
          The princess
          wants WHAT!?

145
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:12,858
   Just what's on that
    little card. No big deal.

146
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:17,562
 No big dea..!? It's a much more
 aggressive weather pattern

147
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,164
        then what was
       originally ordered!

148
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:22,434
     This is very irregular!
       We'll need to-

149
00:08:22,636 --> 00:08:26,538
       No! First we must...
       Wait! We, Oh..!

150
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,872
Take a breath!

151
00:08:29,076 --> 00:08:30,742
Let it out slowly.

152
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:34,145
            Tell the princess
            we will do our best.

153
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:37,116
We're sure you're
doing an excellent job.

154
00:08:37,318 --> 00:08:39,050
Oh! Yeah. Totally.

155
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:42,053
     You're not gonna panic
     and screw it up <i>at all</i>.

156
00:08:43,957 --> 00:08:46,758
    I-I-I'm not built for
    high pressure situations!

157
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,828
       Golly. Sounds like
       you need some help.

158
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,197
   Who are you?

159
00:08:51,398 --> 00:08:53,465
    Somepony who's organized
     enough to handle

160
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:57,035
   the small stuff so you can
   focus on the BIG picture!

161
00:08:57,237 --> 00:09:00,306
       The big...? YES!
       That sounds right!

162
00:09:01,108 --> 00:09:04,976
  Ha, ha. This kind of weather
  has to be handled delicately.

163
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:09,214
    Good thing I'm here. I'll
    take care of <i>everything</i>.

164
00:09:10,484 --> 00:09:11,283
         <i> ♪ [fanfare] ♪</i>

165
00:09:14,755 --> 00:09:15,787
              Whoa!

166
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:19,291
    The Flaming Sky Firework
    Troupe is a marvel.

167
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:21,627
  We take pride in what we do.

168
00:09:22,029 --> 00:09:24,262
    These last-minute changes
     aren't too challenging,

169
00:09:24,364 --> 00:09:24,999
            are they?

170
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:30,235
  Ha! The more challenging, the
   better! We aim to <i>astound</i>.

171
00:09:30,337 --> 00:09:33,606
 Now, if you don't mind, we DO
 have a new routine to prepare.

172
00:09:34,508 --> 00:09:36,575
       Horns at the ready!

173
00:09:36,877 --> 00:09:39,744
               ♪♪

174
00:09:43,784 --> 00:09:45,617
        Very impressive!

175
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:48,119
    Thank you. Unfortunately,
     we have no room

176
00:09:48,221 --> 00:09:52,524
      for anypony else at
      this time. Ahem. I'm sorry?

177
00:09:52,626 --> 00:09:54,059
        Crackle Cossette.

178
00:09:54,161 --> 00:09:56,561
    And I don't want to join
    your silly little troupe.

179
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:58,397
           Pardon me?

180
00:09:58,699 --> 00:10:03,001
 Oh! I meant no offense! It
 just seems a pity for unicorns

181
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:07,672
  to waste their talents on
  something so... inconsequential.

182
00:10:09,643 --> 00:10:11,910
      Unicorns wield <i>magic</i>.

183
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:15,581
    We are the most POWERFUL
     ponies in the land.

184
00:10:15,883 --> 00:10:18,951
   Don't you ever feel you're
    destined for more than...

185
00:10:19,353 --> 00:10:21,352
          ...<i>performances</i>?

186
00:10:24,591 --> 00:10:26,257
    It's all coming together!

187
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:28,126
     I really think this is
      going to be the best

188
00:10:28,228 --> 00:10:30,429
         Summer Sun
        Celebration EVER!

189
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:33,064
         You've done an
        outstanding job!

190
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:35,433
        We've ALL done an
        outstanding job!

191
00:10:35,535 --> 00:10:36,568
       And what about me?

192
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:39,204
  You'll be happy to know that
   I have been watching myself

193
00:10:39,306 --> 00:10:43,308
    all night and I have yet
   to do ONE Discord-y thing!

194
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:46,077
                  Luna: Now that truly
                  <i>is</i> amazing.

195
00:10:46,179 --> 00:10:49,948
           Twilight, we know you
           had, uh, difficulties

196
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:52,584
         using the amulet to
         raise the sun and moon.

197
00:10:52,786 --> 00:10:54,719
              We thought perhaps
              a practice session

198
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:57,155
     before the festivities
     might be in order?

199
00:10:57,557 --> 00:11:02,894
     That's... a good idea.
     Thank you all. So much.

200
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:05,930
               ♪♪

201
00:11:06,032 --> 00:11:07,866
                    I sure am
                    proud'a her.

202
00:11:08,068 --> 00:11:09,968
     Yeah! She
      finally realizes

203
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:11,270
                things will turn
                 out fine,

204
00:11:11,472 --> 00:11:13,071
     even when she isn't
     micromanaging

205
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,105
    every little detail.

206
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,875
     Braeburn?! What's wrong!?

207
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:24,349
   Earth ponies. Sick. Food
   missin'. Can't.... bake... anything...

208
00:11:24,585 --> 00:11:25,884
        Something's wrong
        with the weather!

209
00:11:25,986 --> 00:11:29,054
       Storms, hurricanes,
        fog! You name it.

210
00:11:29,156 --> 00:11:30,822
         It's a disaster
         out there!

211
00:11:30,924 --> 00:11:32,958
       Rarity! Please
       inform Her Highness

212
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,893
        that we will not
        be performing.

213
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,228
       A simple fireworks
       show is beneath us!

214
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,764
     We're BETTER than that.

215
00:11:39,066 --> 00:11:42,100
What the...? Everything
was fine a minute ago.

216
00:11:42,502 --> 00:11:45,004
      Apparently, a lot can
       change in a minute.

217
00:11:45,806 --> 00:11:50,842
               ♪♪

218
00:11:50,944 --> 00:11:53,445
        It's total chaos
        out there!

219
00:11:54,147 --> 00:11:55,480
                      Don't look
                      at me!

220
00:11:55,682 --> 00:11:57,048
      What are we gonna do!?

221
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:58,083
    Twilight: Do about what?

222
00:11:59,887 --> 00:12:02,955
    Ah! What are YOU doing here!?

223
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:05,590
I forgot these.
You guys OK?

224
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:07,826
                 Twilight, we're
                 sorry but-

225
00:12:07,928 --> 00:12:09,894
       But! Er. We don't
       know what to do,

226
00:12:09,996 --> 00:12:11,996
      now that everything's
       all ready!

227
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:13,498
            Ha ha ha!

228
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,167
 I guess I was
TOO organized!

229
00:12:16,269 --> 00:12:18,370
I'll try to come up with
a few last-minute errands

230
00:12:18,472 --> 00:12:20,171
for you before
sunrise.

231
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:22,674
Well, that's a relief!

232
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:26,011
      Explain to me why we
      didn't tell her the truth?

233
00:12:26,213 --> 00:12:28,446
Twilight is finally learning
not to let her stress

234
00:12:28,548 --> 00:12:29,948
get the better of her!

235
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:31,583
If she finds out
everything went wrong,

236
00:12:31,685 --> 00:12:33,251
 it could be
devastating!

237
00:12:33,353 --> 00:12:35,186
             She would be
             so upset!

238
00:12:35,288 --> 00:12:37,122
                She'll totally
                freak out!

239
00:12:37,524 --> 00:12:39,491
                  Well, what do
                  y'all suggest?

240
00:12:39,493 --> 00:12:42,594
Oo-oo-ooh! Let's just fix it
all before she notices!

241
00:12:42,696 --> 00:12:43,895
No lying necessary!

242
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:45,130
                  I guess...

243
00:12:45,432 --> 00:12:46,565
We'd need a miracle.

244
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:49,668
       We HAVE a miracle!
          Don't we?

245
00:12:51,071 --> 00:12:54,239
        I suppose I COULD
        fix everything...

246
00:12:54,641 --> 00:12:56,875
        But isn't the
        real miracle here

247
00:12:56,977 --> 00:13:00,812
     the miracle of teamwork
     and character growth?

248
00:13:02,249 --> 00:13:04,516
Oh, come on!

249
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:07,752
       Discord is right.
       Twilight needs US.

250
00:13:07,854 --> 00:13:09,988
       Whatever happened,
        we can fix this.

251
00:13:11,424 --> 00:13:12,891
What DID happen?

252
00:13:17,564 --> 00:13:20,598
     Best. Road trip. EVER!

253
00:13:25,072 --> 00:13:30,675
               ♪♪

254
00:13:31,845 --> 00:13:33,378
                Even if I was an
                actual doctor,

255
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,179
               I would have no
               idea what's wrong.

256
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:36,615
There's gotta
be a reason.

257
00:13:37,017 --> 00:13:38,517
Something got
'em all sick.

258
00:13:39,019 --> 00:13:40,185
Maybe the food?

259
00:13:40,387 --> 00:13:44,990
    I ate the food too! Does
   that mean I'm sick? Oh, no!

260
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:49,360
       Nope. I feel fine.

261
00:13:52,162 --> 00:13:59,034
<i> ♪ [mysterious music] ♪</i>

262
00:14:01,408 --> 00:14:02,907
               ♪♪

263
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:10,749
♪♪

264
00:14:10,873 --> 00:14:13,673
<i> ♪ [heroic music] ♪</i>

265
00:14:13,753 --> 00:14:15,219
        I don't know how
         this happened!

266
00:14:15,321 --> 00:14:17,789
         I'm going to be
         FIRED for sure!

267
00:14:17,891 --> 00:14:19,557
        Rainbow Dash and
         the Wonderbolts

268
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:22,694
    will have ALL the weather
    rounded up any minute.

269
00:14:22,796 --> 00:14:25,231
         AHHHH! [thud]

270
00:14:25,355 --> 00:14:26,355
         Or not!

271
00:14:29,569 --> 00:14:30,352
            Not here.

272
00:14:30,653 --> 00:14:32,536
  The Archives are in a
  different part of the castle.

273
00:14:37,644 --> 00:14:39,911
        What about aiming
         for perfection?

274
00:14:40,013 --> 00:14:41,880
         We've set our
         sights higher.

275
00:14:42,082 --> 00:14:43,448
     Higher than perfection?

276
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:45,950
<i>Higher</i> than putting
on a silly little show

277
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:47,318
for the other ponies.

278
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:51,489
     But you were so excited
      before! What changed!?

279
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:06,905
♪♪

280
00:15:07,007 --> 00:15:08,873
       You two just enjoy
      the festivities!

281
00:15:08,975 --> 00:15:11,176
     I have a few surprises
      in store for-

282
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:12,877
          Yes, Discord?

283
00:15:12,979 --> 00:15:16,214
   Oh! Well, don't mind me. I'm
    just here for the chaos.

284
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:19,684
    Oh-oh-oh. And here we go!

285
00:15:21,054 --> 00:15:22,654
   What is Rainbow Dash doing?

286
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:26,591
                      Pinkie? Is
                      this soup?

287
00:15:26,693 --> 00:15:29,961
  Yes! I... was
   really hungry?

288
00:15:30,063 --> 00:15:32,864
Nopony understands
wanting to take pride

289
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:35,233
in your work
more than I do!

290
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:36,734
        You could do more
         with your magic

291
00:15:36,836 --> 00:15:38,803
        than make frilly
        dresses!

292
00:15:39,005 --> 00:15:41,739
        Pfft! Nopony makes
         frills anymore!

293
00:15:41,841 --> 00:15:44,075
    This season is actually
    all about simplicity and-

294
00:15:44,177 --> 00:15:46,043
Not the point, Rarity!

295
00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:48,246
Princess!

296
00:15:48,848 --> 00:15:52,450
I BEG your forgiveness.
It's entirely MY fault!

297
00:15:52,752 --> 00:15:53,518
            What is?

298
00:15:55,421 --> 00:15:56,221
          That!

299
00:15:56,623 --> 00:16:00,291
  Oh...um! Just a slight hiccup
   in the weather! Ha, ha.

300
00:16:01,215 --> 00:16:04,415
♪♪

301
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:06,497
Applejack? What
is going on?

302
00:16:06,599 --> 00:16:08,867
               I TOLD y'all this
               was a bad idea

303
00:16:08,969 --> 00:16:11,570
but nopony ever
LISTENS TO ME!

304
00:16:11,972 --> 00:16:13,304
           That's IT!

305
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:17,820
      Ooof!

306
00:16:18,345 --> 00:16:21,179
    I thought everything was
     fine! What is going on!?

307
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:23,582
   Everything <i>was</i> going fine.

308
00:16:23,684 --> 00:16:25,417
    Until it totally wasn't.

309
00:16:25,819 --> 00:16:27,886
         We tried to fix
          it ourselves...

310
00:16:27,988 --> 00:16:29,254
          Why didn't
          you tell me!?

311
00:16:29,556 --> 00:16:31,389
        We didn't want
        you to freak out.

312
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:33,291
      And you thought NOT
      telling me everything

313
00:16:33,393 --> 00:16:35,994
    was a total disaster
    would avoid a freak-out!?

314
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:39,964
 When you say it like that, it
 sounds like a really bad plan.

315
00:16:42,202 --> 00:16:44,102
        Here it comes...

316
00:16:44,704 --> 00:16:48,539
   I know how I used to react.
   But I really have changed!

317
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:50,875
         Panicking won't
         solve anything.

318
00:16:52,712 --> 00:16:55,379
      But we can handle whatever
      problems come our way,

319
00:16:55,481 --> 00:16:57,748
            as long as we handle
            them... together!

320
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:00,251
Celestia: Spoken like a
true leader.

321
00:17:00,453 --> 00:17:01,586
How can we help?

322
00:17:01,988 --> 00:17:03,622
    I love a good to-do list!

323
00:17:04,224 --> 00:17:05,656
       So tell me exactly
        what happened

324
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:09,026
  so we can figure out exactly
   what to do to fix it!

325
00:17:09,128 --> 00:17:11,829
   <i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

326
00:17:11,931 --> 00:17:16,167
               ♪♪

327
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:52,915
               ♪♪

328
00:17:53,974 --> 00:18:06,045
♪♪

329
00:18:07,554 --> 00:18:20,325
               ♪♪

330
00:18:22,034 --> 00:18:23,534
♪♪

331
00:18:24,504 --> 00:18:29,073
♪♪

332
00:18:38,151 --> 00:18:49,823
      <i> ♪ [royal fanfare] ♪</i>

333
00:18:52,932 --> 00:18:55,800
     This celebration has
     always been a reminder

334
00:18:55,902 --> 00:18:57,435
     not to fear the night,

335
00:18:57,637 --> 00:19:00,338
    for there is always a new
    day to look forward to.

336
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:03,007
     But as we look towards
       Equestria's future,

337
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:05,609
      I am sad to say that
     today will be the last

338
00:19:05,711 --> 00:19:07,578
     Summer Sun Celebration.

339
00:19:09,549 --> 00:19:11,816
  ...because there is something
   even more important

340
00:19:11,918 --> 00:19:12,751
          to celebrate.

341
00:19:13,553 --> 00:19:15,820
      There are two ponies
    who have watched over us

342
00:19:16,122 --> 00:19:18,689
    night and day for as
    long as we can remember.

343
00:19:18,891 --> 00:19:22,460
  We will no longer commemorate
 their battle or their reunion.

344
00:19:22,662 --> 00:19:25,263
      Instead, we will take
      this day to celebrate

345
00:19:25,365 --> 00:19:27,432
       how much they mean
        to all of us.

346
00:19:27,734 --> 00:19:30,268
     From this day forward
     today will be known as..

347
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:33,003
       The Festival of
        the Two Sisters!

348
00:19:36,176 --> 00:19:38,142
                   We don't know
                   what to say...

349
00:19:38,244 --> 00:19:43,247
                              ♪♪

350
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:47,952
  Hee hee! A brand-new holiday?
  You're my kinda princess!

351
00:19:48,054 --> 00:19:49,654
I'm just glad we
pulled it off.

352
00:19:49,756 --> 00:19:53,557
About that... We just wanted
to say.. we're real sorry.

353
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:55,493
         You did tell us
         you'd changed.

354
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:58,696
As your friends, we
should have trusted you.

355
00:19:59,098 --> 00:20:01,298
Next time you say you're
not gonna freak out,

356
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,351
we'll believe you.

357
00:20:02,452 --> 00:20:05,103
 Good. Because I'm sure there's
 going to plenty of things

358
00:20:05,205 --> 00:20:07,305
       I'll need my best
       friends' help with.

359
00:20:08,741 --> 00:20:09,540
              Whee!

360
00:20:09,642 --> 00:20:10,708
              Whoa!

361
00:20:11,796 --> 00:20:16,247
  You know, it really does seem
  like you just might be ready

362
00:20:16,349 --> 00:20:20,084
       for whatever comes
       next, Your Majesty.

363
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:25,656
    So...? Did you find what
    you were looking for?

364
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:30,928
 Once again, I've found success
 where you all find failure!

365
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,763
                  I have located
                  what I sought

366
00:20:32,865 --> 00:20:35,900
         and tomorrow I will set
         out to retrieve it.

367
00:20:36,002 --> 00:20:36,902
         When I return,

368
00:20:37,003 --> 00:20:40,903
     Equestria will finally
     be ours for the taking.

369
00:20:41,106 --> 00:20:41,773
      Hmph!

370
00:20:42,275 --> 00:20:44,008
               Oh, stop pouting.

371
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:45,976
      You knew you couldn't
       stay that buff.

372
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,679
 You had to return all the life
   force to those earth ponies

373
00:20:48,781 --> 00:20:50,715
        so Grogar doesn't
        suspect anything.

374
00:20:50,817 --> 00:20:53,117
    I don't have to like it.

375
00:20:53,619 --> 00:20:55,119
       Well, I don't like
     that we worked so hard

376
00:20:55,221 --> 00:20:57,388
   to destroy their party and
    they still pulled it off,

377
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,657
        but you don't see
        ME complaining!

378
00:21:00,159 --> 00:21:03,794
   Our goal wasn't to destroy;
    it was to distract.

379
00:21:04,964 --> 00:21:07,598
      And now we have
      exactly what we need.

380
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,767
           And no time to waste.

381
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:13,337
   We have to master the Bell
     before Grogar returns.

382
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:17,341
 We've managed to stay one step
   ahead of everypony so far...

383
00:21:17,543 --> 00:21:21,879
  You know.. It really was
  super-easy to get all those

384
00:21:21,981 --> 00:21:24,715
       earth ponies and
       pegasi and unicorns

385
00:21:24,817 --> 00:21:26,184
     to turn on each other.

386
00:21:26,286 --> 00:21:31,922
It was, wasn't it. Now <i>that</i>
 is something to think about...

